Klaus Iohannis|Klaus Johannis]], have earned respect as thorough administrators. The party has often cooperated with the [[National Liberal Party (Romania)|National Liberals]], to which Johannis became a member and one of its prime leaders in February, 2013.\n\nAt local administration level, most notably in [[Timi\u0219oara]] ({{lang-de|Temeschburg}}) or [[Baia Mare]] ({{lang-de|Frauenbach}}, the FDGR/DFDR has also co-operated with another Romanian centre-right historical party, namely the [[Christian Democratic National Peasants' Party|PN\u021a-CD]].\n\n== Overview ==\n[[File:Medias Casa Schuller.jpg|thumb|right|The Schuller house ({{lang-de|Das Schullerhaus}}; {{lang-ro|Casa Schuller}}), the seat of the FDGR/DFDR in [[Media\u0219]] ({{lang-de|Mediasch}}), [[Sibiu County]].]]\n\n[[File:RO SB Lutsch house.jpg|thumb|right|The Lutsch house ({{lang-de|Das Lutschhaus}}, {{lang-ro|Casa Lutsch}}), the seat of the FDGR/DFDR in [[Sibiu]] ({{lang-de|Hermannstadt}}).]]\n\nThe history of the German minority in Romania, and more specifically, their presence in the historical region of [[Transylvania]], spans approximately a millennium. Under the blanket term '[[Germans of Romania|Romanian Germans]]' ({{lang-de|Rum\u00e4niendeutsche}}) a wide variety of different regional German-speaking groups are included as follows:\n\n* [[Transylvanian Saxons]];\n* [[Banat Swabians]];\n* [[Satu Mare Swabians|Sathmar Swabians]];\n* [[Bukovina Germans]];\n* [[Transylvanian Landler]];\n* [[Zipser Germans]];\n* [[Regat Germans]] {{NoteTag|The term ''[[Romanian Old Kingdom|Regat]]'' refers to the territorial extent of the Romanian kingdom before [[World War I]].}};\n* [[Dobrujan Germans]];\n* [[Bessarabia Germans]] (former Romanian citizens between 1918 and 1940).\n\nSince the year 2000, the FDGR/DFDR has won offices on both local and regional levels. In [[Sibiu]] ({{lang-de|Hermannstadt}}), the FDGR/DFDR's Klaus Johannis has held the office of mayor from 2000 to 2014. In 2004, the forum gained 60.43% of votes in local elections for the [[Municipiu|Municipal Council]]. In addition, the FDGR/DFDR held 12 out of 23 seats in the Sibiu Municipal Council, forming an absolute majority alongside the [[National Liberal Party (Romania)|PNL]].\n\nFollowing the [[2016 Romanian local elections|2016 local elections]] in [[Sibiu County]] (which has a population of about 450,000 residents), the FDGR/DFDR won 8 out of 33 seats in the [[Counties of Romania|County Council]], where it is the third strongest political faction, after National Liberals and Social Democrats.\n\nThe FDGR/DFDR has also had mayors in office since 2004 in the cities of [[Media\u015f]] ({{lang-de|Mediasch}}) and [[Cisn\u0103die]] ({{lang-de|Heltau}}), as well as in a few villages in [[Satu Mare County|Satu Mare]] ({{lang-de|Sathmar}}) county. The FDGR/DFDR is an associated member of the [[Federal Union of European Nationalities]] and was formerly affiliated with the [[European People's Party group|European People's Party]] ({{lang-de|Europ\u00e4ische Volkspartei}}).\n\n== Presidents ==\n\n* 1990\u20131992: [[:ro:Thomas N\u00e4gler|Thomas N\u00e4gler]]\n* 1992\u20131998: [[:ro:Paul Philippi|Paul Philippi]]\n* 1998\u20132001: [[:ro:Eberhard Wolfgang Wittstock|Eberhard Wolfgang Wittstock]]\n* 2001\u20132013: [[Klaus Iohannis|Klaus Werner Johannis]]\n* 2013\u2013present: [[:ro:Paul-J\u00fcrgen Porr|Paul-J\u00fcrgen Porr]]\n\n== Localities with DFDR mayors ==\n\n[[File:Demokratisches Forum der Deutschen in Kronstadt.jpg|thumb|150px|right|FDGR/DFDR electoral poster in [[Bra\u0219ov]] ({{lang-de|Kronstadt}})]]\n\nAfter the [[2016 Romanian local elections]], the DFDR/FDGR candidates won the following localities:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fdgr.ro/ro/alegeri|title=Rezultatele FDGR \u00een alegerile locale din 2016 (in Romanian)|author=Forumul Democrat al Germanilor din Rom\u00e2nia|work=FDGR/DFDR website|accessdate = April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n\n* [[C\u0103min]] ({{lang-de|Kalmandi}})\n* [[Sanisl\u0103u]] ({{lang-de|Stanislau}})\n* [[Turulung]] ({{lang-de|Turterebesch}})\n* [[Urziceni, Satu Mare|Petre\u015fti]] ({{lang-de|Petrifeld}}) \n* [[Sibiu]] ({{lang-de|Hermannstadt}})\n\n== FDGR/DFDR politicians ==\n* [[Astrid Fodor]], current mayor of Sibiu\n* [[:ro:Martin Bottesch|Martin Bottesch]], President of the Sibiu County Council\n* [[Ovidiu Gan\u021b|Ovidiu Victor Gan\u021b]], member of Parliament and MEP for Romania, 2007\u20132009\n* [[:ro:Daniel Thellmann|Daniel Thellmann]], former mayor of Media\u0219 and founding member of DFDR/FDGR\n* [[Klaus Iohannis|Klaus Johannis]], 5th President of Romania\n* [[:ro:Paul Philippi|Paul Philippi]], theologian and President of FDGR/DFDR\n* [[:ro:Eberhard Wolfgang Wittstock|Eberhard Wolfgang Wittstock]], journalist and former FDGR/DFDR Member of Parliament\n\n== Electoral performance ==\n\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:right width=50%\n!rowspan=2|Election\n!colspan=3|[[Chamber of Deputies (Romania)|Chamber of Deputies]]\n!colspan=3|[[Senate of Romania|Senate]]\n|-\n!Votes\n!%\n!Seats\n!Votes\n!%\n!Seats\n|-\n|align=center|[[1990 Romanian general election|1990]]||38,768||0.28||1||19,105||0.14||0\n|-\n|align=center|[[1992 Romanian general election|1992]]||34,685||0.32||1||{{n/a}}||{{n/a}}||{{n/a}}\n|-\n|align=center|[[1996 Romanian general election|1996]]||23,888||0.20||1||{{n/a}}||{{n/a}}||{{n/a}}\n|-\n|align=center|[[2000 Romanian general election|2000]]||40,844||0.31||1||{{n/a}}||{{n/a}}||{{n/a}}\n|-\n|align=center|[[2004 Romanian general election|2004]]||36,166||0.35||1||{{n/a}}||{{n/a}}||{{n/a}}\n|-\n|align=center|[[2008 Romanian legislative election|2008]]||23,190||0.30||1||{{n/a}}||{{n/a}}||{{n/a}}\n|-\n|align=center|[[2012 Romanian legislative election|2012]]||39,175||0.53||1||{{n/a}}||{{n/a}}||{{n/a}}\n|-\n|align=center|[[2016 Romanian legislative election|2016]]||12,375||0.18||1||{{n/a}}||{{n/a}}||{{n/a}}\n|-\n|align=center|[[Next Romanian legislative election|2020]]||TBD||TBD||TBD||TBD||TBD||TBD\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*